Q: Can I upload multiple files at once?
A: Yes! Click "Add file" → "Upload files". You can drag and drop multiple files from your computer.

Q: What if I want to upload a folder?
A: On GitHub website, you can only upload files, not folders. But you can create folders by typing the folder name in the filename box like folder_name/file.py

Q: Is this really "git"?
A: Yes! GitHub's website does all the git commands for you behind the scenes. You're still using git, just through a web interface.

Q: Can people really install my tool with pip?
A: Yes! As long as you have setup.py and pasgen.py, anyone can run pip install git+https://github.com/yourusername/pasgen.git

Q: Do I need to do anything else?
A: Nope! Your tool is live and ready for the world to use!
